cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper focuses on studying the effect of class imbalance and order on crowdsourced relevance judgments, which is a common problem in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The relevance judgments are related to the identification of positive labels, which is a task commonly performed in natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The experiment design and findings may also be relevant to social computing (cs.SI) as it involves studying the behavior of crowd workers.
